# Performance and Architecture Standards

## General Principles
- Follow [KISS (Keep It Simple, Stupid)](mdc:#KISS) - prefer simpler solutions over complex ones
- Apply [YAGNI (You Aren't Gonna Need It)](mdc:#YAGNI) - don't add functionality until necessary
- Practice [DRY (Don't Repeat Yourself)](mdc:#DRY) - extract common logic to reusable functions
- Maintain [SOLID principles](mdc:#SOLID) within a functional paradigm
- Write [Self-Documenting Code](mdc:#Self-Doc) - see also generic.mdc

## Bundle Size Management
- Use React.lazy with Suspense for feature-level code splitting
- Import specific components from libraries instead of entire packages
- Include bundle analysis in CI pipeline with size budgets per chunk
- Add tree-shaking hints to unused exports (`/*#__PURE__*/`)
- Use dynamic imports for rarely accessed features

## Performance Optimization
- Implement virtualization for all list components with >20 items
- useMemo/useCallback: see **code-standard.mdc** (only when needed; avoid by default).
- React.memo for pure presentational components
- Use windowing techniques for large datasets (e.g. react-window)
- Profile components with React Profiler and optimize re-renders
- Apply skeleton loading states consistently across all async operations
- Follow [Zustand and Memo Optimization](mdc:zustand-memo-optimization.mdc) guidelines to prevent unnecessary re-renders

## API Layer Abstraction
- Create pure function-based API utilities rather than classes
- Use React Router loader/fetcher for data fetching (see api-request-pattern.mdc, api-integration-pattern.mdc)
- Create specific response DTOs with proper typing; validate with type guards in loaders
- Add retry logic for transient failures where appropriate
- Use composition over inheritance for API behavior customization

## State Management Scale
- Use Zustand for global application state
- Store only data in store state; export actions as standalone functions that use `store.setState()` / `store.getState()` (see [Zustand and Memo Optimization](mdc:zustand-memo-optimization.mdc))
- For one-off initialization from loader/API result, prefer pure functions that call `store.setState()` directly (e.g. `setInitialToastInfo(result)`); use hooks that return a setter only when the setter needs hook context or to be passed as a dependency
- Create domain-specific slices for state isolation
- Implement observer pattern using pure functions
- Define clear boundaries between global and local state
- Avoid prop drilling deeper than 3 levels
- Apply immutability principles consistently

## Functional Programming Principles <a name="SOLID"></a>
- Use pure functions throughout the codebase
- Prefer composition over inheritance
- Avoid side effects outside designated effect handlers
- Use immutable data structures
- Leverage function composition and higher-order functions
- Implement proper error handling with Either/Result patterns
- Prefer declarative over imperative code

## <a name="KISS"></a>KISS - Keep It Simple, Stupid
- Break complex problems into smaller, manageable pieces
- Use established patterns over clever solutions
- Minimize nested conditions and complex expressions
- Use descriptive naming to convey intent
- Limit each function to doing one thing well

## <a name="YAGNI"></a>YAGNI - You Aren't Gonna Need It
- Implement features only when they're needed, not when they might be needed
- Avoid speculative generality that adds unused flexibility
- Remove dead or unused code regularly
- Don't over-engineer solutions based on future requirements
- Start with the simplest implementation that meets requirements
- Avoid creating complex folder structures for simple components
- Don't add barrel files (index.ts) unless actually needed for export organization
- Keep component organization flat when components are tightly coupled and only used together
- Refactor toward complexity only when proven necessary

## <a name="DRY"></a>DRY - Don't Repeat Yourself
- Extract common logic into reusable functions
- Use hooks and composition for shared component logic (avoid unnecessary HoFs per code-standard.mdc)
- Create utility functions for repeated calculations
- Establish shared constants for values used in multiple places
- Use custom hooks to share stateful logic between components

## <a name="Self-Doc"></a>Self-Documenting Code
- Choose descriptive variable and function names
- Structure code to reveal intent (revealing module pattern)
- Extract complex expressions into well-named variables
- Use TypeScript types to document data structures
- Only add comments for "why" not "what" or "how"

## Accessibility Standards
- Add a11y testing (e.g. axe-core with vitest) to component test suites
- Enforce proper keyboard navigation for all interactive elements
- Implement focus trapping for modals and popups
- Add skip navigation links for keyboard users
- Ensure all interactive elements have appropriate ARIA attributes
- Test with screen readers as part of the pre-commit checklist

## Build Performance
- Optimize Vite configuration for faster rebuilds
- Enable persistent cache between builds
- Configure dependency pre-bundling for common libraries
- Implement parallel builds for multi-core utilization
- Replace heavy dependencies with lighter alternatives
- Monitor and optimize CSS size (e.g. Tailwind purge / build-time pruning)

